---
import DocsLayout from '../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL.replace(/\/$/, '');
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Course Creators"
  description="Build and publish courses using the engine's course.md format — from directory layout to question banks, test generators, and the PR workflow."
  chapterId="creators"
>
  <nav slot="toc">
    <a href="#layout"        class="docs-toc-link">Course Layout</a>
    <a href="#frontmatter"   class="docs-toc-link">course.md Reference</a>
    <a href="#questions"     class="docs-toc-link">Question Types</a>
    <a href="#generators"    class="docs-toc-link">Test Generators</a>
    <a href="#assets"        class="docs-toc-link">Assets</a>
    <a href="#pr-workflow"   class="docs-toc-link">PR Workflow</a>
    <a href="#checklist"     class="docs-toc-link">Checklist</a>
  </nav>

  <section id="layout" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">
      Course Directory Layout
      <span class="docs-section-badge" style="background:color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 12%,transparent);color:#a78bfa;border:1px solid color-mix(in srgb,#a78bfa 30%,transparent)">Setup</span>
    </h2>
    <p>Every course lives under <code>engine/courses/&#123;slug&#125;/</code>. Copy the template to start:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">bash</span></div>
      <code>cp -r engine/courses/template engine/courses/your-slug</code>
    </div>
    <p>Full directory structure:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">tree</span></div>
      <code>engine/courses/your-slug/
├── course.md                ← single source of truth (edit this)
├── course.json              ← auto-generated on merge (do not edit)
├── contributors.json        ← auto-generated on merge (do not edit)
└── assets/
    ├── images/              (1200×630 banner + diagrams)
    ├── starter/             (starter code per chapter)
    │   └── ch-01/
    │       ├── starter.py
    │       └── README.md
    ├── solutions/           (reference solutions — gitignore these!)
    ├── tests/               (dynamic test generator scripts)
    ├── slides/              (PDF slide decks)
    └── data/                (CSV, JSON datasets)</code>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--danger">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">🔒</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Never commit <code>assets/solutions/</code>. Add it to <code>.gitignore</code> or keep it on a private branch. The grader never reads this directory — it runs test cases, not solution comparisons.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="frontmatter" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">course.md Frontmatter Reference</h2>
    <p><code>course.md</code> uses YAML frontmatter. All fields are validated by <code>validate-pr.yml</code> on PR open. The Markdown body (after the closing <code>---</code>) contains your full course content — lessons, chapters, and question banks.</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Field</th><th>Type</th><th>Req</th><th>Description</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>meta.slug</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>URL-safe, lowercase, hyphens only. Permanent — never change after publish.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.title</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>Display name shown on the site.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.version</code></td><td>semver</td><td>✓</td><td>Bump on breaking curriculum changes.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.description</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>One paragraph (&lt;200 words) — what students will know after completing this.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.track</code></td><td>enum</td><td>✓</td><td><code>foundations</code> <code>languages</code> <code>web</code> <code>backend</code> <code>systems</code> <code>networks</code> <code>data</code> <code>security</code> <code>architecture</code> <code>creative</code> <code>emerging</code> <code>applied</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.difficulty</code></td><td>enum</td><td>✓</td><td><code>beginner</code> <code>intermediate</code> <code>advanced</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.tags</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>✓</td><td>Topic tags for filtering. Lowercase-hyphens.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.prerequisites</code></td><td>string[]</td><td>✓</td><td>Array of course slugs that must be completed first. Use <code>[]</code> for none.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.estimated_hours</code></td><td>number</td><td>✓</td><td>Total study time in hours.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.thumbnail</code></td><td>path</td><td></td><td>Path to 1200×630 PNG/JPG banner.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.license</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>Default: <code>CC BY-SA 4.0</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>meta.repo</code></td><td>URL</td><td>✓</td><td>GitHub repo URL for live star/fork counts.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>contributors[].name</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>Display name.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>contributors[].github</code></td><td>string</td><td>✓</td><td>GitHub username — canonical identity.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>contributors[].role</code></td><td>enum</td><td>✓</td><td><code>author</code> <code>reviewer</code> <code>translator</code> <code>illustrator</code> <code>maintainer</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>certificate.requires_all_chapter_tests</code></td><td>bool</td><td>✓</td><td>Must all chapter tests be passed?</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>certificate.min_overall_score</code></td><td>0–100</td><td>✓</td><td>Minimum average score to receive certificate.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>certificate.requires_final_project</code></td><td>bool</td><td>✓</td><td>Is a final project required?</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>certificate.final_test</code></td><td>ChapterTest</td><td></td><td>Optional grand final exam — unlocks after all chapter tests pass.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="questions" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Question Types</h2>
    <p>All question types are supported in <code>chapter_test.questions[]</code> and lesson-level <code>quiz.questions[]</code>:</p>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Type</th><th>Key fields</th><th>Grading</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>mcq</code></td><td><code>options: string[]</code>, <code>answer: "A"</code></td><td>Exact match. 1 point.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>multi</code></td><td><code>options: string[]</code>, <code>answer: ["A","C"]</code></td><td>Partial credit: <code>correct_selected / total_correct × points</code></td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>true_false</code></td><td><code>answer: true</code></td><td>Exact match. 1 point.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>short</code></td><td><code>keywords: string[]</code>, <code>min_keywords: 2</code></td><td>Keyword match. Zero if &lt; min_keywords matched.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>code</code></td><td><code>language</code>, <code>test_cases[]</code> or <code>test_generator</code></td><td><code>passed / total × points</code>. Docker sandbox.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
    <p>Supported sandbox languages: <code>python</code> <code>javascript</code> <code>bash</code> <code>java</code> <code>go</code> <code>rust</code> <code>c</code> <code>cpp</code></p>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--info">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">ℹ️</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">Short-answer questions use keyword matching — no AI, no semantic analysis. List at least 3 distinct keywords per question. Set <code>min_keywords: 2</code> to require at least 2 matches for any credit.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="generators" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Dynamic Test Generators</h2>
    <p>Instead of static test cases (which students can memorize), use a seed-based generator. The grader calls it with a fresh random seed each attempt:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">bash</span></div>
      <code>python assets/tests/q5-sort-gen.py --seed 42 --count 10</code>
    </div>
    <p>The generator must print a JSON array to stdout:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">json</span></div>
      <code>[
  &#123;"input": "[3,1,4]", "expected_output": "[1,3,4]", "description": "basic sort"&#125;,
  &#123;"input": "[5,5,5]", "expected_output": "[5,5,5]", "hidden": true&#125;
]</code>
    </div>
    <p>Reference it in your <code>course.md</code> question:</p>
    <div class="docs-pre">
      <div class="docs-pre__bar"><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__dot"></span><span class="docs-pre__lang">yaml</span></div>
      <code>- type: code
  language: python
  points: 10
  test_generator: ./assets/tests/q5-sort-gen.py
  starter_code: |
    def sort_list(nums):
        pass</code>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="assets" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Assets</h2>
    <div class="docs-table-wrap">
      <table class="docs-table">
        <thead><tr><th>Directory</th><th>Contents</th><th>Notes</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody>
          <tr><td><code>assets/images/</code></td><td>Banner, diagrams, screenshots</td><td>Banner must be 1200×630 px. Reference as <code>./assets/images/banner.png</code> in <code>meta.thumbnail</code>.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/starter/</code></td><td>Code scaffolding per chapter</td><td>Organize by chapter: <code>starter/ch-01/starter.py</code>. Handed to students.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/solutions/</code></td><td>Reference solutions</td><td><strong>Gitignore or private branch.</strong> Grader never reads this.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/tests/</code></td><td>Dynamic test generators</td><td>Committed — run on CI, not student machines.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/slides/</code></td><td>PDF slide decks</td><td>Link with full raw GitHub URL.</td></tr>
          <tr><td><code>assets/data/</code></td><td>CSV, JSON datasets</td><td>For data-focused exercises.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="pr-workflow" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">PR Workflow</h2>
    <div class="docs-steps" style="--ch-color:#a78bfa">
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">1</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Create a branch and copy the template</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc"><code>git checkout -b course/your-slug</code> then <code>cp -r engine/courses/template engine/courses/your-slug</code></p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">2</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Edit course.md and add assets</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc">Fill in all required frontmatter fields. Write your lessons, chapter tests, and questions in the Markdown body. Add assets to the <code>assets/</code> directory.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">3</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Open a PR → validate-pr.yml runs</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc">Automatically parses <code>course.md</code>, validates all fields, checks for engine path tampering, and posts a validation report as a PR comment. Fix any errors and push.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docs-step">
        <div class="docs-step__line"><div class="docs-step__num">4</div><div class="docs-step__connector"></div></div>
        <div class="docs-step__body">
          <p class="docs-step__title">Merge → automated publish</p>
          <p class="docs-step__desc"><code>course-publish.yml</code> generates <code>course.json</code> + <code>contributors.json</code>. <code>sync-site-data.yml</code> aggregates all data. <code>deploy-site.yml</code> rebuilds. Live in ~90 seconds.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="docs-callout docs-callout--danger">
      <span class="docs-callout__icon">🔒</span>
      <div class="docs-callout__body">The slug in <code>meta.slug</code> is permanent once published. Changing it is a breaking change that invalidates all existing enrollment issues for that course.</div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="checklist" class="docs-section">
    <h2 class="docs-section-title">Course Creator Checklist</h2>
    <ul class="docs-checklist">
      <li>Slug is lowercase-hyphen and globally unique</li>
      <li>Description is &lt;200 words and accurately describes learning outcomes</li>
      <li>Track slug is one of the 12 valid values</li>
      <li>All prerequisites reference published course slugs</li>
      <li>Every chapter has a <code>chapter_test</code> with at least 3 questions</li>
      <li><code>pass_score</code> is set (50–90% recommended)</li>
      <li>Code questions have at least 5 test cases or a generator script</li>
      <li>Short-answer questions have ≥ 3 keywords defined</li>
      <li>Reference solutions are gitignored or on a private branch</li>
      <li>Banner image is 1200×630 px</li>
      <li>Your GitHub username appears in <code>contributors[].github</code></li>
      <li><code>estimated_hours</code> is realistic (cross-check against lesson durations)</li>
    </ul>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
